article.headline: Denver 66, Southern Utah 53
article.story: DENVER (AP) -- Erik Benzel scored 17 points from the perimeter and Brett Starkey powered inside for 16 points to lead Denver to a 66-53 victory over Southern Utah Saturday. Southern Utah's David Palmer scored 33, including 8-for-11 from the 3-point range. Denver (3-2) made only three turnovers and shot 57.1 percent, including three consecutive three-pointers, to take a 38-24 lead at intermission. Southern Utah (2-3) shot 60 percent early in the second half to close the gap to nine points, 45-36, as the Pioneers cooled off and missed six of nine attempts. Benzel and Starkey's accuracy, Zeljko Zupic's rebounding, and Rodney Billups' tight defense enabled Denver to rebuild its lead. Palmer scored 17 of his team's first 22 points and seven straight late in the game to draw the Thunderbirds within 11, 57-46. But a 3-pointer by Benzel kept Southern Utah at bay. Along with his scoring, the 6-foot-1 Benzel grabbed nine rebounds and made four steals and four assists. Zupic hit for 11 points and snared 12 rebounds. Denver finished with a 48 percent mark from the field.
